  "text": "Forster et al. conducted a three-year matched cohort study of 75 000 NHS Health Check participants. [CITATION_1] They found a marked increase in the recording of all four specified risk factors (smoking, blood pressure, BMI and cholesterol) compared to non-participants. There was a significant increase in detection of hypercholesterolaemia and, to a lesser extent, obesity and hypertension, as well as a significant reduction in gender and deprivation inequalities in risk recording.",
